ange [1, n] by leveraging a counting mechanism to navigate through the tree of numbers in lexicographical order. The `getCntNodes` function calculates the number of nodes in the subtree rooted at `current` without having to explicitly list them, making it suitable for large values of n up to 10^9.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}